ZH: 我们应该理会他的困境。
EN: We should take into consideration his predicament.

ZH: 老师不理会我的提问。
EN: The teacher ignored my question.

ZH: 他对别人的意见毫不理会。
EN: He pays no attention to other people's opinions.

ZH: 请理会一下我的建议。
EN: Please take my suggestion into account.

ZH: 我们应该理会他的苦衷。
EN: We should understand his difficulties.

ZH: 现在不是理会感情问题的时候。
EN: Now is not the time to concern ourselves with emotional issues.

ZH: 他总是不理会我的感受。
EN: He always disregards my feelings.

ZH: 别人的误解我们不用理会。
EN: We don't need to worry about other people's misunderstandings.

ZH: 如果你理会妈妈的话，她会很高兴的。
EN: If you pay attention to mom, she will be very happy.

ZH: 我们不能只顾自己，还要理会别人。
EN: We can't just think about ourselves, we also need to consider others.

ZH: 尽管他说了很多话，我不会去理会。
EN: Even though he said a lot, I won't pay attention.

ZH: 我们必须理会他的感受，不能伤害他。
EN: We must consider his feelings and not hurt him.

ZH: 你不能对别人的请求漠不理会。
EN: You can't ignore other people's requests.

ZH: 如果你理会别人的需要，他们会更喜欢你。
EN: If you take others' needs into account, they will like you more.

ZH: 我们要多理会老人的感受。
EN: We should pay more attention to the feelings of the elderly.

ZH: 不要以为没人理会你，其实还有很多人关心你。
EN: Don't think nobody cares about you, many people actually do.

ZH: 管理会议就是要能理会大家的需求。
EN: Managing meetings means being able to understand everyone's needs.

ZH: 我们需要理会环境保护的重要性。
EN: We need to understand the importance of environmental protection.

ZH: 怎样理会别人的话是一门艺术。
EN: Knowing how to understand others' words is an art.

ZH: 理会别人的观点不代表赞同他们。
EN: Understanding others' viewpoints doesn't mean agreeing with them.

ZH: 我们应该理会自己的行为对别人的影响。
EN: We should consider the impact of our actions on others.
